'''Anders Olsen''' (1718 on the [[Senja (island)|island of Senja]], [[Norway]] - 1786 at [[Igaliko]], [[Greenland]]) was a [[Norway|Norwegian]] [[Merchant|trader]], explorer and colonial administrator, who founded several important towns in [[Greenland]] including [[Qaqortoq]] (Julianehåb) and [[Maniitsoq]] (Sukkertoppen) as well as the village of [[Igaliku]]. <ref>{{cite web|url= https://nbl.snl.no/Anders_Olsen|title =Anders Olsen|publisher = Norsk biografisk leksikon |author= Finn Erhard Johannessen|accessdate= December 1,  2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.greenland.com/en/destinations/south-greenland/igaliku/|title=Igaliku|publisher=Greenland.com|date= December 1, 2016}}</ref>

